02:37:11,767 --> 02:37:18,167
Empress of Hindustan,
jodhaabai has arrived in Diwaan-E-Aam!

1225
02:37:52,967 --> 02:37:56,433
I am overwhelmed with
happiness to see you here.

1226
02:37:57,167 --> 02:37:58,700
I had to come.

1227
02:37:59,567 --> 02:38:02,300
After all, you have won my heart!

1228
02:38:21,633 --> 02:38:22,767
Your Majesty...

1229
02:38:23,433 --> 02:38:27,300
...today your people have
wholly accepted you in their hearts.

1230
02:38:28,967 --> 02:38:32,433
And hence, your subjects, most humbly...

1231
02:38:32,967 --> 02:38:34,433
...wish to bestow on you...

1232
02:38:35,033 --> 02:38:36,967
...the title of... 'Akbar'!

1233
02:38:37,567 --> 02:38:40,033
jalaluddin Mohammad 'Akbar'!

1234
02:38:47,167 --> 02:38:49,633
The title pleases me very much.

1235
02:38:51,033 --> 02:38:53,767
I accept it with gratitude.

1236
02:38:55,167 --> 02:38:59,900
- jalaluddin Mohammad Akbar!
- Long live!

1237
02:39:00,233 --> 02:39:01,633
Akbar!

1238
02:39:02,567 --> 02:39:07,033
Every heart bears witness
to our Emperor's generosity

1239
02:39:07,433 --> 02:39:14,300
Wherever he treads,
he showers gold on his path

1240
02:39:23,700 --> 02:39:28,300
We welcome you in our hearts

1241
02:39:52,033 --> 02:39:55,500
Your religion is love

1242
02:39:56,767 --> 02:40:00,300
You rule many hearts

1243
02:40:10,900 --> 02:40:14,500
No praise can describe you

1244
02:40:15,633 --> 02:40:20,433
You are the confluence of all traditions

1245
02:40:34,633 --> 02:40:38,900
We welcome you in our hearts

1246
02:40:43,833 --> 02:40:46,167
O great and magnificent Emperor!

1247
02:42:31,633 --> 02:42:33,567
The Emperor has been struck by an arrow!

1248
02:42:37,500 --> 02:42:39,033
There he is!

1249
02:43:56,967 --> 02:44:01,900
Allow His Majesty to rest. We will
keep you informed of his progress.

1250
02:44:33,433 --> 02:44:36,700
'l am very pleased. No praise
will do justice to your work.'

1251
02:44:37,033 --> 02:44:39,767
'Delhi is within our reach now.
Saadir Adaasi'

1252
02:44:44,167 --> 02:44:48,167
The arrow's poison is spreading.

1253
02:44:49,500 --> 02:44:51,967
His temperature isn't coming down.

1254
02:45:05,900 --> 02:45:08,767
Who could have attempted
to kill jalaluddin?

1255
02:45:09,167 --> 02:45:13,967
- Never mind! My concern is Rajputana.
- Meaning?

1256
02:45:14,633 --> 02:45:17,567
If jalaluddin survives...

1257
02:45:18,767 --> 02:45:22,700
...the Mughal army will spare no one.

1258
02:45:23,900 --> 02:45:25,033
And if he dies...

1259
02:45:25,967 --> 02:45:29,433
...the Afghans and UZbeks
won't let this opportunity slip by.

1260
02:45:30,433 --> 02:45:32,300
That's so true, Ranaji.

1261
02:45:32,900 --> 02:45:35,433
It will be wise to ignore
the needs of others...

1262
02:45:35,833 --> 02:45:37,700
...and safeguard our own provinces.

1263
02:45:38,300 --> 02:45:39,633
Sujamal...

1264
02:45:40,967 --> 02:45:42,633
...we would've helped you...

1265
02:45:44,300 --> 02:45:46,300
...but circumstances have changed.

1266
02:45:47,700 --> 02:45:52,033
And anyway,
your struggle is no more political...

1267
02:45:52,433 --> 02:45:54,233
...it has become a family feud.

1268
02:45:56,033 --> 02:45:59,500
You must work alone to regain
your share of Amer's throne!

1269
02:46:00,700 --> 02:46:04,633
We can only offer you
our best wishes, nothing more!

1270
02:46:18,767 --> 02:46:21,233
jodhaa, his condition is worsening.

1271
02:46:35,300 --> 02:46:36,900
O Lord Krishna...

1272
02:47:07,300 --> 02:47:09,700
The Emperor has
regained consciousness!

1273
02:47:26,500 --> 02:47:28,300
May His Majesty live long!

1274
02:47:32,300 --> 02:47:34,433
May God give you a long life!

1275
02:47:34,967 --> 02:47:37,500
- Please rest.
- The Emperor is well again.

1276
02:47:37,833 --> 02:47:40,833
The Emperor is well again?
The Emperor is well again!

1277
02:47:47,700 --> 02:47:53,033
jalal, countless thanks to Allah
for giving you a new life.

1278
02:47:54,567 --> 02:47:55,567
Mother...

1279
02:47:56,500 --> 02:48:00,367
Don't strain, son. You need rest.

1280
02:48:36,100 --> 02:48:39,967
Turn the nib and draw a thicker line...

1281
02:48:50,700 --> 02:48:52,367
Why did you call me here?

1282
02:48:53,233 --> 02:48:55,500
I will show you why.
Disperse!

1283
02:48:56,967 --> 02:48:58,433
Please be seated.

1284
02:49:10,833 --> 02:49:12,700
I have made something special for you.

1285
02:49:13,500 --> 02:49:15,300
I'm learning calligraphy.

1286
02:49:15,700 --> 02:49:19,100
These are the first words
I have learnt to write.

1287
02:49:21,033 --> 02:49:24,500
Allah be praised. It is beautiful!

1288
02:49:27,500 --> 02:49:29,967
This calligraphy... this writing...

1289
02:49:31,167 --> 02:49:33,767
...whatever is written, is beautiful.

1290
02:49:35,700 --> 02:49:39,433
Since its your writing,
why don't you read it aloud.

1291
02:49:40,233 --> 02:49:42,700
No, you must read it yourself.

1292
02:49:48,300 --> 02:49:50,433
There's something
you must know, jodhaa.

1293
02:49:52,500 --> 02:49:54,167
The truth is...

1294
02:49:55,500 --> 02:49:57,567
...I cannot read or write!

1295
02:49:59,500 --> 02:50:05,167
The battlefield never allowed me
to learn, how to read or write.

1296
02:50:08,967 --> 02:50:10,367
So now will you read it?

1297
02:50:14,567 --> 02:50:16,300
You won't agree this way.

1298
02:50:19,967 --> 02:50:21,300
It's an order!

1299
02:50:24,300 --> 02:50:25,167
Read it!

1300
02:50:26,033 --> 02:50:28,700
A wife does not take
her husband's name.

1301
02:50:35,700 --> 02:50:37,300
Look into my eyes and say it.

1302
02:50:42,700 --> 02:50:49,767
jalaluddin Mohammed Akbar.

1303
02:50:54,233 --> 02:50:55,767
"Jodhaa" ...

1304
02:50:58,433 --> 02:51:00,100
I want to ask you something...

1305
02:51:01,833 --> 02:51:03,100
Please do...

1306
02:51:04,300 --> 02:51:07,833
Not here. Come with me.

1307
02:51:34,033 --> 02:51:36,700
What was it that you wanted to ask?

1308
02:51:38,567 --> 02:51:40,700
I am waiting for the right moment...

1309
02:52:07,233 --> 02:52:08,967
Do you love me?

1310
02:52:22,500 --> 02:52:24,033
Yes, I do.

1311
02:52:24,967 --> 02:52:26,367
And you?

1312
02:52:27,567 --> 02:52:29,967
I love you deeply!

1313
02:52:39,700 --> 02:52:43,700
In the folds of these moments

1314
02:52:46,167 --> 02:52:50,700
Is a relationship so pure

1315
02:52:52,500 --> 02:53:00,033
Like a prayer of
love the angels recite

1316
02:53:02,100 --> 02:53:07,033
The earth is silent
The sky is perpleXed

1317
02:53:08,700 --> 02:53:13,700
There is light shining from earth to sky

1318
02:53:17,500 --> 02:53:25,033
Songs fill the stillness.
There is beauty in your every gesture

1319
02:53:25,700 --> 02:53:30,033
There is love floating in the air

1320
02:54:23,700 --> 02:54:26,500
What love is this?

1321
02:54:27,033 --> 02:54:29,033
What dream is this?

1322
02:54:30,433 --> 02:54:36,300
What flood of feeling is this?

1323
02:54:49,567 --> 02:54:58,833
The days have changed. And nights
too. The meaning of life has changed

1324
02:55:00,567 --> 02:55:06,033
In the folds of these moments...

1325
02:55:39,033 --> 02:55:46,300
What has time done to me?
Changed my very being

1326
02:55:48,700 --> 02:55:55,967
You have won me I found you

1327
02:55:58,300 --> 02:56:04,167
Melting like two gentle melodies

1328
02:56:04,567 --> 02:56:10,567
A rhythm, not slow, not fast

1329
02:56:11,033 --> 02:56:13,567
In the flame of fire

1330
02:56:13,833 --> 02:56:22,833
Our bodies and souls
burn in the flame of love

1331
02:56:42,700 --> 02:56:48,433
In my garden of dreams

1332
02:56:50,167 --> 02:56:56,967
Spring came only because of you

1333
02:56:58,167 --> 02:57:04,567
The flowers had my colours

1334
02:57:05,700 --> 02:57:13,700
But their fragrance has come from you

1335
02:57:16,500 --> 02:57:22,567
What desire and emotion is this?

1336
02:57:23,300 --> 02:57:28,767
Why is the heart so restless?
Why is the heart so impatient?

1337
02:57:42,500 --> 02:57:51,500
The days have changed. And nights
too. The meaning of life has changed

1338
02:57:53,500 --> 02:57:58,233
In the folds of these moments...

1339
02:58:44,700 --> 02:58:49,567
We missed our last chance.
That incompetent marksman!

1340
02:58:51,167 --> 02:58:55,500
- You mean?
- Yes! It was l, who sent the assassin.

1341
02:58:56,700 --> 02:58:59,433
Be gone! Our efforts have gone waste.

1342
02:59:01,433 --> 02:59:03,767
I'm glad my sister is not widowed.

1343
02:59:04,433 --> 02:59:08,567
Sujamal! What's with you? You don't
even know whose side you are on.

1344
02:59:09,567 --> 02:59:10,967
Greed has blinded you!

1345
02:59:11,567 --> 02:59:15,767
I want my rightful share of Amer!
You don't know which side to take!

1346
02:59:16,833 --> 02:59:19,300
The Emperor is your brother-in-law,
Sharifuddin Hussain.

1347
02:59:19,833 --> 02:59:22,833
Personal relations cannot
interfere with my goals.

1348
02:59:24,033 --> 02:59:26,833
You will soon discover
I am on your side...

1349
02:59:27,967 --> 02:59:30,233
...I want to see you
on Amer's throne...

1350
02:59:31,300 --> 02:59:35,700
...and you will see me
on Delhi's throne. Our pact is firm!

1351
02:59:36,967 --> 02:59:39,300
We have only one option now.

1352
02:59:40,033 --> 02:59:44,033
Attack Amer at once!
We won't get a better opportunity.

1353
02:59:46,833 --> 02:59:48,300
Are you with me?

1354
02:59:54,033 --> 02:59:55,033
Yes.

1355
03:00:00,833 --> 03:00:02,300
Sharifuddin Hussain!

1356
03:00:16,967 --> 03:00:19,967
jalal knows you were behind
the assassination attempt.

1357
03:00:20,500 --> 03:00:25,167
He is furious.
Soldiers are coming for us!

1358
03:00:26,367 --> 03:00:28,300
Have no fear, Saadir Adaasi Sahib.

1359
03:00:29,567 --> 03:00:32,833
Before Agra, we must seiZe Amer!

1360
03:00:33,300 --> 03:00:34,500
Amer?

1361
03:00:36,033 --> 03:00:38,833
Will Sujamal help you once he is crowned?

1362
03:00:40,833 --> 03:00:44,967
Once Amer is in our hands,
we will finish Sujamal.

1363
03:00:49,500 --> 03:00:52,567
Sharifuddin has planned
an attack on Amer.

1364
03:00:53,167 --> 03:00:55,300
With Sujamal taking on his side.

1365
03:00:56,433 --> 03:01:00,233
End this conflict and
give Sujamal his rightful share.

1366
03:01:03,233 --> 03:01:04,700
Have no fear!

1367
03:01:05,500 --> 03:01:06,433
Yes.

1368
03:01:09,500 --> 03:01:10,967
Now about Sharifuddin...

1369
03:01:13,700 --> 03:01:17,700
...he must be stopped in Merta,
before he reaches Amer.

1370
03:01:42,833 --> 03:01:43,833
Banu?

1371
03:01:44,033 --> 03:01:48,500
Time is scarce.
My husband can kill Sujamal anytime.

1372
03:01:50,567 --> 03:01:53,700
jodhaa, stop this battle!

1373
03:01:54,500 --> 03:01:57,700
Or else three families
will drown in their own blood.

1374
03:02:00,700 --> 03:02:02,233
We have to go!

1375
03:02:03,567 --> 03:02:06,500
The battlefield is dangerous.
Do not go!

1376
03:02:10,033 --> 03:02:15,367
Todarmalji, my mind is made up.
I must go. Do not worry.

1377
03:02:23,033 --> 03:02:23,967
Halt!

1378
03:02:40,767 --> 03:02:45,033
Your Majesty, dust is rising
on the northern horiZon...

1379
03:03:02,700 --> 03:03:04,033
How far are they?

1380
03:03:05,300 --> 03:03:07,367
About three miles.

1381
03:03:12,300 --> 03:03:14,967
Two miles...

1382
03:03:18,300 --> 03:03:20,700
He has arrived too soon.

1383
03:03:24,233 --> 03:03:26,833
One mile!

1384
03:03:34,700 --> 03:03:36,233
Halt!

1385
03:03:58,967 --> 03:04:02,967
Your Majesty,
the archers await your command.

1386
03:04:04,300 --> 03:04:05,367
No!

1387
03:04:07,500 --> 03:04:09,167
I want peace, not war.

1388
03:04:10,500 --> 03:04:13,967
Chughtai Khan! Raise the peace flag!

1389
03:04:16,567 --> 03:04:18,233
Pardon me, Your Majesty...

1390
03:04:18,433 --> 03:04:21,833
...Sharifuddin will misunderstand.
He might assume we are weak.

1391
03:04:23,100 --> 03:04:24,967
That's precisely what I want.

1392
03:04:25,567 --> 03:04:28,700
He must get the wrong idea
and commit a mistake.

1393
03:04:29,567 --> 03:04:31,833
I understood. Raise the peace flag!

1394
03:04:41,967 --> 03:04:45,567
I knew jalaluddin
would want to negotiate.

1395
03:04:46,367 --> 03:04:47,967
- Manjum Khan!
- Yes, Your Majesty.

1396
03:04:48,433 --> 03:04:50,833
Raise our flag in acceptance.

1397
03:04:52,300 --> 03:04:55,433
And set camp here!

1398
03:04:56,433 --> 03:04:58,300
Allah, protect us!

1399
03:05:10,700 --> 03:05:12,500
He deliberately did
not use elephants.

1400
03:05:12,833 --> 03:05:14,833
Because they would
have slowed down his pace.

1401
03:05:15,033 --> 03:05:19,033
Their army has much food.
They can survive a long time.

1402
03:05:19,567 --> 03:05:21,967
They can eXtend the battle
longer than us.

1403
03:05:26,433 --> 03:05:30,100
Many of our soldiers have been
misguided to join Sharifuddin's army.

1404
03:05:32,167 --> 03:05:34,033
We have to bring them back!

1405
03:05:35,967 --> 03:05:40,500
A great battle is won
without shedding a single drop of blood.

1406
03:06:06,033 --> 03:06:07,833
- Is everything ready?
- Yes, Your Majesty.

1407
03:06:08,300 --> 03:06:09,567
Make no mistake.

1408
03:06:10,300 --> 03:06:14,700
You will infiltrate the Emperor's
army and find a way into his tent...

1409
03:06:15,833 --> 03:06:19,833
...and at the opportune moment,
kill the Emperor!

1410
03:06:21,567 --> 03:06:23,767
Also, jalaluddin has told Bharmal...

1411
03:06:24,433 --> 03:06:27,967
...to grant Sujamal
his rights to Amer's throne.

1412
03:06:28,500 --> 03:06:31,567
Make sure Sujamal
learns nothing of this.

1413
03:06:33,500 --> 03:06:37,967
Once we get rid of the Emperor,
Sujamal comes neXt.

1414
03:06:47,233 --> 03:06:48,300
Don't ask questions!

1415
03:06:50,233 --> 03:06:51,967
We are withdrawing
our support of Sharifuddin.

1416
03:06:52,367 --> 03:06:53,500
As you command.

1417
03:06:56,167 --> 03:06:59,967
Take our men and fight alongside
jalaluddin's army.

1418
03:07:01,100 --> 03:07:02,567
Hurry! There is very little time.

1419
03:07:02,833 --> 03:07:04,367
As you command...

1420
03:07:15,100 --> 03:07:16,767
What is the meaning of this?

1421
03:07:20,100 --> 03:07:24,500
- Kumbhaa?
- What happened? Surprised?

1422
03:07:26,367 --> 03:07:30,100
Wasn't he the one you sent to warn jalaluddin?

1423
03:07:30,567 --> 03:07:33,167
Yes. Because I wanted to stop you.

1424
03:07:34,233 --> 03:07:38,100
If you're a true warrior, then fight
jalaluddin on the battlefield.

1425
03:07:38,967 --> 03:07:40,167
Not by conspiracy!

1426
03:07:40,700 --> 03:07:41,833
Not by conspiracy?

1427
03:07:43,500 --> 03:07:46,033
When you asked me
to help overthrow King Bharmal...

1428
03:07:46,500 --> 03:07:47,700
...wasn't that a conspiracy?

1429
03:07:49,100 --> 03:07:50,300
Where was your loyalty then?

1430
03:09:05,967 --> 03:09:08,167
On your guard!

1431
03:09:10,300 --> 03:09:11,567
Horsemen approaching!

1432
03:09:14,500 --> 03:09:15,833
It's Sujamal!

1433
03:09:22,167 --> 03:09:23,300
Sujamal!

1434
03:09:44,033 --> 03:09:45,033
Warn the Emperor!

1435
03:09:45,500 --> 03:09:48,433
Bhagwan Das, pull out the arrows!

1436
03:10:07,967 --> 03:10:08,967
Is this Sujamal?

1437
03:10:10,033 --> 03:10:11,100
Yes, Your Majesty.

1438
03:10:15,967 --> 03:10:21,500
Sharifuddin has sent an assassin
disguised as a Royal Guard to kill you.

1439
03:10:28,967 --> 03:10:30,033
Take him away!

1440
03:10:43,300 --> 03:10:45,567
Thank you, Uncle. I am grateful to you.

1441
03:10:46,500 --> 03:10:48,433
You agreed to offer me my share...

1442
03:10:50,300 --> 03:10:55,100
I made a mistake... in judging you

1443
03:10:58,700 --> 03:10:59,700
O Allah!

1444
03:11:02,100 --> 03:11:03,700
jodhaa will be distraught!

1445
03:11:04,100 --> 03:11:06,033
She betrayed me!

1446
03:11:07,700 --> 03:11:09,700
No, Sujamal. You are mistaken.

1447
03:11:10,833 --> 03:11:13,833
It was l, who mistrusted her,
and wanted you arrested.

1448
03:11:14,767 --> 03:11:17,300
- jodhaa is not at fault.
- What?

1449
03:11:54,833 --> 03:12:00,833
jodhaa, I misunderstood you
and doubted your integrity...

1450
03:12:06,300 --> 03:12:07,767
...forgive me...

1451
03:12:10,033 --> 03:12:11,300
Don't say that!

1452
03:12:12,233 --> 03:12:13,967
I misunderstood you...

1453
03:12:16,033 --> 03:12:18,233
...I hurt your honour...

1454
03:12:22,300 --> 03:12:23,700
No, brother!

1455
03:12:29,500 --> 03:12:31,700
May you stay forever happy!

1456
03:12:40,300 --> 03:12:43,100
You are... a great man!

1457
03:12:44,367 --> 03:12:48,300
I was wrong...
to have not understood you.

1458
03:12:49,300 --> 03:12:51,500
What you have done for jodhaa...

1459
03:12:52,033 --> 03:12:59,767
...will make future generations
honour and respect you...

1460
03:13:29,567 --> 03:13:30,500
Banu...

1461
03:13:31,833 --> 03:13:33,500
...Sharifuddin is a rebel.

1462
03:13:36,300 --> 03:13:39,700
He has committed treason against me.

1463
03:13:42,033 --> 03:13:46,767
The only punishment
for such a man is death.

1464
03:13:49,033 --> 03:13:51,033
justice demands that I kill him.

1465
03:13:51,700 --> 03:13:55,233
I don't know if he is right or wrong.

1466
03:13:56,500 --> 03:13:59,433
But the need of the hour is...

1467
03:14:00,733 --> 03:14:03,833
...to let your spirit of forgiveness
guide your decision.

1468
03:14:05,300 --> 03:14:08,833
O Allah, what must I do?

1469
03:14:10,733 --> 03:14:13,133
First Adham and now Sharifuddin...

1470
03:14:15,133 --> 03:14:20,533
...why do my close ones have
to fall under the shadow of my sword?

1471
03:14:40,667 --> 03:14:42,533
I eXpected this behaviour from you...

1472
03:14:43,467 --> 03:14:46,067
...but it is your misfortune
that I survived.

1473
03:14:47,033 --> 03:14:50,033
I could have made you Governor
of other provinces besides Ajmer.

1474
03:14:51,733 --> 03:14:55,933
Rebellion results in only one thing...
and that is bloodshed.

1475
03:14:56,433 --> 03:15:01,033
Didn't you think of 'bloodshed'
when you mercilessly killed Adham Khan?

1476
03:15:01,433 --> 03:15:03,133
That was a different matter,
Sharifuddin.

1477
03:15:03,833 --> 03:15:05,000
How unfair!

1478
03:15:05,667 --> 03:15:09,733
You can't state the 'rules of the game'
and make the moves too.

1479
03:15:10,933 --> 03:15:13,267
This time I decide the rules.

1480
03:15:15,467 --> 03:15:16,267
I am listening.

1481
03:15:16,667 --> 03:15:20,467
If you want, we can prevent bloodshed.

1482
03:15:22,000 --> 03:15:22,933
And how is that?

1483
03:15:23,533 --> 03:15:25,467
Fight me!

1484
03:15:26,933 --> 03:15:29,000
In an arm-to-arm combat.

1485
03:15:30,467 --> 03:15:32,933
If I win,
then Hindustan will be mine.

1486
03:15:36,067 --> 03:15:40,533
And if I lose,
I will leave this country forever!

1487
03:15:45,467 --> 03:15:47,000
I accept!

1488
03:15:50,800 --> 03:15:55,467
This is no way to crush a revolt.
Why did you accept?

1489
03:15:56,467 --> 03:15:58,267
To prevent bloodshed.

1490
03:15:58,733 --> 03:16:04,200
Forgive me, Your Majesty, you forget
Sharifuddin is fierce and vicious.

1491
03:16:05,133 --> 03:16:06,467
I'm aware of that.

1492
03:16:08,200 --> 03:16:09,533
He is a strong man.

1493
03:16:11,133 --> 03:16:14,067
But I won't let Hindustan
fall in the wrong hands!

1494
03:21:54,467 --> 03:21:56,000
Sharifuddin!

1495
03:21:59,000 --> 03:22:01,667
If you were not my brother-in-law...

1496
03:22:03,067 --> 03:22:05,267
...this spear would
have gone through you!

1497
03:22:10,333 --> 03:22:12,467
Only for my sister's sake...

1498
03:22:13,800 --> 03:22:15,467
...I forgive you!

1499
03:22:28,667 --> 03:22:31,267
I am taking back
your provinces from you.

1500
03:22:36,267 --> 03:22:39,667
You will not be allowed to take any
administrative decisions from now on.

1501
03:22:40,667 --> 03:22:42,067
As you command.

1502
03:22:44,933 --> 03:22:50,000
And all your life...
you will remain loyal to me!

1503
03:22:52,133 --> 03:22:53,267
Yes, Your Majesty!

1504
03:22:56,133 --> 03:23:02,800
- Emperor jalaluddin Mohammad Akbar!
- Long live!

1505
03:23:36,933 --> 03:23:39,333
Respected Saadir Adaasi Sahib...

1506
03:23:41,000 --> 03:23:43,067
...the happiness of life...

1507
03:23:44,467 --> 03:23:47,333
...cannot be divided
on religious grounds.

1508
03:23:54,267 --> 03:23:57,467
I am a follower of lslam... a Muslim!

1509
03:23:59,067 --> 03:24:02,667
And yet, I bow my head,
in respect for every religion.

1510
03:24:05,733 --> 03:24:08,200
The people of my Empire are free...

1511
03:24:09,733 --> 03:24:12,133
...to worship and practice
their religions.

1512
03:24:15,933 --> 03:24:20,733
But it is a shame
you failed to understand me.

1513
03:24:24,400 --> 03:24:26,267
Now it is my wish.

1514
03:24:28,200 --> 03:24:33,200
You dedicate your life to
Allah and travel to Holy Mecca!

1515
03:24:53,933 --> 03:24:56,800
Now I request
the Rajput Empress of Hindustan...

1516
03:24:57,400 --> 03:24:59,400
...to join me here.

1517
03:25:07,533 --> 03:25:11,333
To all present and the Mughal empire,
I say this for the last time -

1518
03:25:13,667 --> 03:25:15,800
Queen jodhaa is a Hindu Rajput.

1519
03:25:17,533 --> 03:25:19,000
She is my wife.

1520
03:25:19,933 --> 03:25:22,400
And the Empress of Hindustan!

1521
03:25:23,667 --> 03:25:27,267
Any act against her, is an act
against the Mughal empire.

1522
03:25:30,667 --> 03:25:33,000
Let one more thing
be known to one and all!

1523
03:25:34,133 --> 03:25:39,200
Respect and tolerance
of every religion...

1524
03:25:40,267 --> 03:25:42,933
...will make the future
of Hindustan glorious!

1525
03:25:43,733 --> 03:25:45,800
So be it!

1526
03:25:50,267 --> 03:25:51,800
Anything else for the day,
Chughtai Khan?

1527
03:25:52,467 --> 03:25:54,533
Only a prayer for your good health.

1528
03:25:57,933 --> 03:26:00,333
This was the story of jodhaa Akbar.

1529
03:26:02,200 --> 03:26:04,667
Their love story is
not a part of folklore.

1530
03:26:05,733 --> 03:26:08,000
Nor is their love ever discussed.

1531
03:26:09,533 --> 03:26:13,667
Perhaps, it is because...
history never gave them any importance.

1532
03:26:14,667 --> 03:26:16,533
But the truth is...

1533
03:26:17,000 --> 03:26:20,000
... that jodhaa and Akbar, together...

1534
03:26:20,467 --> 03:26:21,667
... silently...

1535
03:26:22,200 --> 03:26:24,667
... made history!

